clusters.title: Democrats Announce Plans to Boycott Trump's State of the Union
clusters.summary: A number of Democratic lawmakers have declared their intention to boycott President Trump's upcoming State of the Union address. This decision reflects ongoing tensions between the Democratic Party and the Trump administration, with some members citing concerns over the President's policies and rhetoric. The boycott is seen as a symbolic protest against the current administration's actions and approach to governance.

clusters.title: Mark Zuckerberg Testifies in Trial on Social Media Addiction Claims
clusters.summary: Mark Zuckerberg is set to testify in a landmark trial in Los Angeles regarding allegations that social media platforms contribute to addiction among children and adolescents. The case, which has garnered significant attention, raises important questions about the impact of social media on youth mental health and the responsibilities of tech companies. The outcome could have far-reaching implications for regulations surrounding social media usage and child safety.
